brokerageName: Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Starck Real Estate
description: Step into this gorgeous corner unit located in Chicago's famous 400 E Randolph St. Unit 930. This 2 bed, 2 bath spacious condo offers  sweeping views of the city's beautiful skyline. Entire condo has been freshly painted and newly installed Lifeproof Vinyl Plank (sustainable) flooring throughout. Kitchen has been remodeled with opening the space to the family room while adding a large, eat-in breakfast bar with built-in wine fridge. Other features include Corian countertops, brand new Bosch dishwasher, matching stove and microwave, custom fitted Subzero fridge/freezer and updated  white cabinets that open up to the expansive dining. Currently the space is being used as an office area. The spacious primary suite is certain to wow with oversized closets. En suite bath boasts a new vanity/sink.The second bedroom is perfectly positioned within the condo and can accommodate a queen-size bed. Be sure to step out onto your oversized balcony so you can enjoy the serene, yet spectacular views of the city. Over-sized closets of plenty and storage are all finished with Custom Closets or Elfa designed. Building offers incredible luxury amenities that include the "400 East Fitness & Spa"-racquetball, basketball, ping-pong, year-round sunny indoor pool -sun deck, party room, business center, library, children's playroom, cardio equipment, machine weights, free weights, massage therapist (by appt.), steam room, sauna and whirlpool, bike rooms and package delivery service. Parking is $220 per month and 30 min free guest parking. Additionally, walk to Millennium, Grant and Daley Park, Michigan Ave. and State Street shopping and entertainment. Easy access to Chicago's Lakefront, Navy Pier, and bike/running paths. All you have to do is move-in and unpack. Welcome home!
